# Technical Notes

This document summarises the analytical reasoning behind the NHS RTT Operational Pressure Analysis project.

## Pressure Score Construction

The pressure score combines three system indicators:

* Total waiting list size  
* Percentage of patients waiting beyond 18 weeks  
* Percentage of patients waiting beyond 52 weeks

These metrics capture different dimensions of operational strain:

Waiting list size reflects demand backlog.

18-week breaches indicate system performance against the constitutional treatment target.

52-week waits signal severe system bottlenecks and potential patient harm risk.

Combining these indicators allows a single interpretable index representing overall system pressure.

## Design Philosophy

The analysis prioritises interpretability and decision support rather than predictive modelling.

The objective is to translate publicly available operational statistics into structured escalation frameworks that can support capacity planning and backlog recovery strategy.
